        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12209",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I thought I have coded this class and I should be asked\/assigned to issues of Date\/Locale and so on ??\n\nAnyway...\nFor checking if a date input is a proper date there are already functions:\n\nZend_Locale_Format::isDate();\nZend_Locale_Format::isTime();\n\nand additionally all integer values will be accepted.\n\nSo the rework of isDate is not that heavy... \nOf course I think not all input variants are supported by now, but about 90%-95% should do correct.\nSo this will do it for a first release.\n\nPseudocode :\n{code}\nfunction isDate($date, $format = null, $locale = null) \n{\n    if (is_number($date)) {\n        return true;\n    }\n\n    if (!Zend_Locale::isLocale($locale)) {\n        \/\/ get default locale if not set\n        $locale = new Zend_Locale();\n        $locale = $locale->toString();\n    }\n\n    $result = Zend_Locale_Format::isDate($date, $format, $locale);\n    if (is_array($result)) {\n        return true;\n    }\n    return false;\n}\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-12T16:31:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-12T16:31:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12245",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks, Thomas; I've committed what I hope to be approaching a solution for this issue based on what you've provided here:\n\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/fisheye\/browse\/Zend_Framework_Laboratory\/Zend_Filter\/library\/Zend\/Validate\/Date.php?r=44\n\nIf this ends up being incorrect, as evidenced from future unit testing, we can open new issues as needed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-15T13:53:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-15T13:53:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12246",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's always a pleasure to help...\n\nTo mention:\nIf something is wrong with the date-checking I would have to check this within Zend_Locale_Format as this is the generic date\/time parsing function for the framework.\n\nIt's also used within Zend_Date and Zend_Calendar.\nSo an error would also show up in these classes, not only in Zend_Validate.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-01-15T14:25:07.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-01-15T14:25:07.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12712",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "After chatting with Darby, I suggest either adopting something like Ralf's lightweight version of this class, or restricting Zend_Validate_Date to using Zend_Locale_Format::isDate() like this:\n\n1) choose a default format of 'yMd'\n2) avoid using locales\n3) replace non-numeric characters from the input with \n4) call Zend_Locale_Format::isDate($inputString, $format, null);",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-13T14:43:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-13T14:43:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12713",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "See ZF-895 for a list of factors affecting use of Zend_Locale_Format::isDate()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-13T14:44:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-13T14:44:58.000+0000"
                }
            ]
